  "prompt": "What are some cute names to call your boyfriend in Spanish?",
  "response": "Here are some cute names you can call your boyfriend in Spanish:\n\n1. **Amor** - Love\n2. **Cielo** - Heaven\n3. **Coraz\u00f3n** - Heart\n4. **G\u00fcerito** (or **G\u00fcerito**) - Light-skinned or blonde guy (often used affectionately)\n5. **Chiquito** - Little one\n6. **Beb\u00e9** - Baby\n7. **Principe** - Prince\n8. **Mi Rey** - My King\n9. **Cachorro** - Puppy (used affectionately)\n10. **Dulce** - Sweet (literally \"sweet\" or \"candy\")\n11. **Papi** - Daddy (used in an affectionate way)\n12. **Osito** - Little bear\n13. **Lindo** - Cute/Pretty\n14. **Tesoro** - Treasure\n15. **Marido** - Husband (often used playfully even if not married)\n\nFeel free to mix and match or adapt them to fit your relationship!",
